{"title_page": "Football in Sri Lanka", "text_new": "{{Infobox sport overview\n| title         = Football in Sri Lanka\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| union         = [[Football Federation of Sri Lanka]]\n| country       = [[Sri Lanka]]\n| sport         = [[Association football|Football]]\n| noncountry    = \n| nationalteam  = [[Sri Lanka national football team|Sri Lanka]]\n| repteam       = \n| nickname      = \n| first         = 1890\n| registered    = \n| clubs         = <!-- COMPETITIONS -->\n| national_list = \n| club_list     = \n* [[Sri Lanka Football Premier League]]\n* [[Sri Lanka FA Cup]]\n| intl_list     = <!-- AUDIENCE RECORDS -->\n* [[SAFF Championship]]\n* [[Bangabandhu Cup]]\n| match         = <!-- single match audience record -->\n| league        = <!-- league audience record -->\n| fan_org       = <!-- fan organization -->\n}}\n'''[[association football|Football]]''' in [[Sri Lanka]] is mainly played at a semi-professional and recreational level. Despite not being as well-regarded as the country's [[Cricket in Sri Lanka|cricket]] team, football is the third biggest sport in Sri Lanka (after cricket and [[Rugby union in Sri Lanka|rugby union]]).\n\n==Governing Body==\n\nThe [[Football Federation of Sri Lanka]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Hafiz Marikar |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/sports/history-football-sri-lanka |title=History of football in Sri Lanka &#124; Daily News Online : Sri Lanka's National News |publisher=Dailynews.lk |date=2013-07-18 |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/120129/Sports/spt14.html |title=An appeal to the Minister of Sports to resurrect Sri Lanka Football |publisher=Sundaytimes.lk |date= |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/130623/sports/sri-lankas-first-international-win-at-football-49901.html |title=Sri Lanka\u2019s first international win at football &#124; The Sundaytimes Sri Lanka |publisher=Sundaytimes.lk |date=2013-06-23 |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/afp/131010/football-sri-lanka-eyes-new-start-after-graft-scandal |title=Football: Sri Lanka eyes new start after graft scandal |publisher=GlobalPost |date=2013-10-10 |accessdate=2013-12-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305072713/http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/afp/131010/football-sri-lanka-eyes-new-start-after-graft-scandal |archivedate=2016-03-05 }}</ref> is the governing body for football in the country. The association administers the [[Sri Lanka national football team|national football team]] as well as the [[Sri Lanka Football Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.colomboherald.com/sports/fifa-failed-to-probe-sri-lanka-football-corruption |title=Fifa \u2018failed to probe\u2019 Sri Lanka football corruption &#124; Colombo Herald |publisher=Colomboherald.com |date=2011-09-02 |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/sinhala/news/story/2011/08/110826_football_corruption.shtml |title=BBCSinhala.com &#124; Sandeshaya &#124; Fifa 'failed to probe' Sri Lanka football corruption |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Football in Sri Lanka}}\n{{Asia in topic|Football in}}\n\n[[Category:Football in Sri Lanka| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sport overview\n| title         = Football in Sri Lanka\n| image         = \n| caption       = \n| union         = [[Football Federation of Sri Lanka]]\n| country       = [[Sri Lanka]]\n| sport         = [[Association football|Football]]\n| noncountry    = \n| nationalteam  = [[Sri Lanka national football team|Sri Lanka]]\n| repteam       = \n| nickname      = \n| first         = 1890\n| registered    = \n| clubs         = <!-- COMPETITIONS -->\n| national_list = \n| club_list     = \n* [[Sri Lanka Football Premier League]]\n* [[Sri Lanka FA Cup]]\n| intl_list     = <!-- AUDIENCE RECORDS -->\n* [[SAFF Championship]]\n* [[Bangabandhu Cup]]\n| match         = <!-- single match audience record -->\n| league        = <!-- league audience record -->\n| fan_org       = <!-- fan organization -->\n}}\n'''[[association football|Football]]''' in [[Sri Lanka]] is mainly played at a semi-professional and recreational level. Despite not being as well-regarded as the country's [[Cricket in Sri Lanka|cricket]] team, football is the third biggest sport in Sri Lanka (after cricket and [[Rugby union in Sri Lanka|rugby union]]).\n\n==Governing Body==\n\nThe [[Football Federation of Sri Lanka]] <ref>{{cite web|author=Hafiz Marikar |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/sports/history-football-sri-lanka |title=History of football in Sri Lanka &#124; Daily News Online : Sri Lanka's National News |publisher=Dailynews.lk |date=2013-07-18 |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/120129/Sports/spt14.html |title=An appeal to the Minister of Sports to resurrect Sri Lanka Football |publisher=Sundaytimes.lk |date= |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/130623/sports/sri-lankas-first-international-win-at-football-49901.html |title=Sri Lanka\u2019s first international win at football &#124; The Sundaytimes Sri Lanka |publisher=Sundaytimes.lk |date=2013-06-23 |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/afp/131010/football-sri-lanka-eyes-new-start-after-graft-scandal |title=Football: Sri Lanka eyes new start after graft scandal |publisher=GlobalPost |date=2013-10-10 |accessdate=2013-12-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305072713/http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/afp/131010/football-sri-lanka-eyes-new-start-after-graft-scandal |archivedate=2016-03-05 }}</ref> is the governing body for football in the country. The association administers the [[Sri Lanka national football team|national football team]] as well as the [[Sri Lanka Football Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.co